  "prompt": "Is it true that Socrates was considered as a prophet in Islam?",
  "response": "No, Socrates is not considered a prophet in Islam. Prophets in Islam are individuals chosen by God to deliver His messages and guidance to humanity, and these figures are specifically mentioned in the Quran and Hadith. Socrates, a classical Greek philosopher, is known for his contributions to Western philosophy and his method of questioning and dialogue, but he is not recognized as a prophet within Islamic tradition. Prophets acknowledged in Islam include figures such as Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, Jesus, and Muhammad, among others.",
